{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01LgoMhQUtDgYUzQa9Daj2BK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented for US-015:\n\n## Summary\n\n**US-015 - Strain-rate tensor computation in Step1** is complete. All acceptance criteria are met:\n\n### Changes made:\n1. **`physics/kernels/step1.cu`** -- Extended K_Step1 kernel to compute the symmetric strain-rate tensor D for GRANULAR particles in the same neighbor loop as density. Accumulates 6 components (Dxx, Dyy, Dzz, Dxy, Dxz, Dyz) using `m_j/rho_j` weighting and spiky gradient. PostCalc computes `gamma_dot = sqrt(2 * D:D)` and writes to `shear_rate_out`. Non-GRANULAR particles get 0.\n\n2. **`step1.py`** -- Updated `compute_step1()` signature with new inputs (velocity, density_in, packed_info) and outputs (shear_rate_out). Returns `(density, shear_rate)` tuple.\n\n3. **`simulation.py`** -- Updated step1 call to pass sorted velocity, density (from previous step, None on first frame), and packed_info.\n\n4. **`test_step1.py`** -- Updated all 11 existing density tests for new signature; added 3 new strain-rate tests.\n\n### Test results (all 15 pass):\n- **Stationary sand**: gamma_dot = 0.0 (exact zero)\n- **Shear flow** (SR=10.0): interior particles produce gamma_dot = 9.56 (4.4% error vs analytical)\n- **Non-GRANULAR**: all shear_rates exactly 0.0\n- **500K mixed particles**: no CUDA errors, all values finite\n\n<promise>COMPLETE</promise>"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":418,"cache_read_input_tokens":131059,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":418},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb47956f-dbff-4960-8452-8e302b089f1c","uuid":"27cec070-7afb-44db-8cde-bd37d5cc0be1"}
